#### 다양한 방법



```python
hc2 <- hclust(dist(x)^2, method = "complete")   #최장 연결법
plot(hc2, labels = crime$city,main = "dendrogram : Complete Linkage Method", xlab='', sub='')

hc3 <- hclust(dist(x)^2, method = "centroid")   #중심법
plot(hc3, labels = crime$city,main = "dendrogram : Centroid Method", xlab='', sub='')

hc4 <- hclust(dist(x)^2, method = "ward.D")   #Ward
plot(hc4, labels = crime$city,main = "dendrogram : Ward", xlab='', sub='')

hc5 <- hclust(dist(x)^2, method = "average")   #평균법
plot(hc5, labels = crime$city,main = "dendrogram : Average Method", xlab='', sub='')

hc6 <- hclust(dist(x)^2, method = "median")   #중앙값법
plot(hc6, labels = crime$city,main = "dendrogram : Median Method", xlab='', sub='')
```

### 표준화


거리 기준으로 하면 표준화는 당연히 해야함



```python
sc_x <- scale(x)  ## 표준화 
```


```python
hc2_sc <- hclust(dist(sc_x)^2, method = "complete")   #최장 연결법
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(hc2, labels = crime$city, hang = 0.1,
     main = "dendrogram : longest connect")

plot(hc2_sc, labels = crime$city, hang = 0.1,
     main = "dendrogram : longest connnect, scale")
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>

결과 조금 달라짐



```python
c1.num <- 3
hc2.result <- cutree(hc2, k = c1.num) #최장 연결법 결과
hc2_sc.result <- cutree(hc2_sc, k = c1.num) #최장 연결법 결과
```


```python
plot(x, pch =  c(15,16,17)[hc2.result], col = hc2.result, main = "longest connect")
plot(x, pch =  c(15,16,17)[hc2_sc.result], col = hc2_sc.result, main = "longest connnect, scale")
```

k-means는 초기 중심값이 중요  

밑에 누를때마다 결과 바뀌는 것을 볼 수 있음  

결론 : 안정하지 않다



```python
par(mfrow=c(2,3))
data_k <-  kmeans(crime[,c(3,4)] ,
                  centers = 3)
plot(crime[,c(3,4)], pch = 16, col =  data_k$cluster, 
     main = round(data_k$tot.withinss,2),
     xaxt='n', yaxt='n',
     xlab='', ylab='')
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>

같은 값 나오게 하기 위해 seed num 고정  

nstart 는 알아서 20(20썼으니까)번 돌린다음에 가장 좋은 값으로 골라줌



```python
par(mfrow=c(2,3))
set.seed(4)
data_k <-  kmeans(crime[,c(3,4)],
                  centers = 3, nstart = 20)
plot(crime[,c(3,4)], pch = 16, col =  data_k$cluster, 
     main = round(data_k$tot.withinss,2),
     xaxt='n', yaxt='n',
     xlab='', ylab='')
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>


```python
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
crime$cluster <- data_k$cluster
plot(crime[,c(3,4)], 
     pch = crime$cluster-1, 
     col = crime$cluster, 
     main = "K-means clustering")
points(data_k$centers, cex=2, col=c(1,2,3), pch=c(15,16,17))
text(crime[,c(3,4)], labels = crime$city, adj = -0.2, cex = 0.8)
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>

가운데 큰 것들은 중심 표시

#### construct clusers 




```python
kmeans.fit = kmeans(sam,centers=2)
new.kmeans.fit = kmeans(new.sam,centers=2)
pam.fit = pam(sam,2)
new.pam.fit = pam(new.sam,2)
```


```python
# plots 
list.plot = list() 
list.plot[[1]] = fviz_cluster(kmeans.fit,
                              sam, 
                              main='K-means w/o outlier')+theme_bw()
list.plot[[3]] = fviz_cluster(new.kmeans.fit,
                              new.sam, 
                              main='K-means w/ outlier') +theme_bw()
list.plot[[2]] = fviz_cluster(pam.fit,sam, main='K-medoids w/o outlier')+theme_bw()
list.plot[[4]] = fviz_cluster(new.pam.fit,new.sam, main='K-medoids w/ outlier')+theme_bw()
plot_grid(plotlist = list.plot, ncol = 2)
```

<img src="data:image/png;base64,"/>

결과 해석 : k-means는 outlier 떔에 결과 바뀌어버림
